# Django Country Detection by IP

This Django project detects the user's country based on their public IP address using external APIs like ip-api or ipify. The country is then displayed on the website, alongside all available blog posts.

## Features

- Detects the user's country based on their public IP address.
- Uses the ip-api or ipify API for country detection.
- Displays blog posts from the database along with the detected country.

## Setup Instructions

Follow the steps below to set up this project locally.

### Prerequisites

Make sure you have the following installed on your machine:

- Python 3.x 
- Django
- pip (Python package manager)

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/abhayrathor12/Assignment.git
cd your-project-directory

# run this command to download the dependies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# run this command to create table in db
python manage.py migrate


### 2. Getting the Data from csv Run this command
python manage.py import_blogs path_to_your_csv


# run this command to run the app
python manage.py runserver